Playbook = Single YAML file
Play = set of taks to be run on hosts
Task = action to be performed on host (execute a command, run a script, install a package, restart the server)

#list modules ansible-doc -l

Modules groups:  

System (systemd, service, make, hostname, ping, mount) 
Commands (Command, Script)
Files (Find, File, Acl, Archive)
Database (Mongodb, Mysql, Postgresql)
Cloud (Amazon, Azure, Docker, Openstack, Google)
Windows (Win_command, Win_copy)

tasks:
	- name: this is a first task with command module 
	  #command: free_form parameter
	  command: cat resolv.conf chdir=/etc


#### Ansible Idempotency= repeat the operation have the same result, Module are Idempotent 
